The 2019 logo is still used on the official Warner Bros. website and the 2019 Warner Bros. logo is still see on social media Twitter and YouTube, for example at Warner Bros. Pictures. In addition, the 2019 Warner Bros. logo is also used, for example in the Barbie Movie or Meg 2: The Trench and also Wonka according to the Trailer. So I wouldn't say that the 2019 logo is already being changed to the 2023 Warner Bros. logo

But is the logo really no longer the logo from 2016 to 2019? Because onscreen it is still the logo from 2016 to 2019, which is why I would say that the logo from 2016 to 2019 would be more correct, since it is also the onscreen logo that you generally see.

message: If universal is known as anything else general it is "Universal Studio". Universal is known as Universal Pictures or as Universal Studios. For example, in the credits of Universal films, it is "Universal Studios". In media reports it's either Universal Pictures or Universal Studios, but mostly Universal Pictures. But Universal has never been seen in media reports, credits or otherwise as "Universal City Studios LLC", which is why Universal Studios should be at the beginning of the article.
